The shrine was founded in {{ill|718|ja|718th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Yōrō 2)<ref>{{Cite book|title=Nagano Prefecture History: Hokushin Region|publisher=Nagano Prefectural History Association|year=1971|page=322}}</ref>. It is situated at the summit of Mount Minakami and is referred to collectively as '''Minakami Shrine''', encompassing the main {{ill|Kumano Izuhaya Shrine|ja|熊野出速雄神社|12=draft|12=draft}}, Jijū Shrine, and associated sub-shrines<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.matsushiro-kankou.com/spot/spot-049/|title=Minakami Shrine|publisher=Shinshu Matsushiro Tourism Association|accessdate=November 2, 2024}}</ref>.

The main hall was rebuilt in {{ill|1389|ja|1389th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Kōō 1) and designated as a cultural property of Nagano Prefecture on {{ill|August 15, 1994|ja|1994th year 8月15日|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref name=":0" />.

== Enshrined Deities ==
* {{ill|Izuhaya no Mikoto|ja|出速雄命|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Izanagi|ja|伊邪那岐尊|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Izanami|ja|伊邪那美尊|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Kumano Gongen|lt=Hayatama no Mikoto|ja|速玉男命|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Yomotsu Wakesu no Mikoto|ja|予母都事解之男命|12=draft|12=draft}}

== Sub-Shrines ==
* '''Jijū Shrine'''
** Dedicated to Jijū Dai, the third son of Uchiyama Mitsuhisa, lord of {{ill|Uchiyama Castle|ja|内山城|12=draft|12=draft}}. Following the fall of the Uchiyama clan, he retreated to Mount Minakami, adopting the title Dainichi-ji Wago-in Yūken. He later became known as Jijū Tengu-bō and enshrined Jijūbō Daitengu Myōō in {{ill|1556|ja|1556th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Kōji 2)<ref name=":0" />.
* {{ill|Fuji Sengen Shrine|ja|富士浅間神社|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Tenmangū|ja|天満宮|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Benzaiten|ja|弁天社|12=draft|12=draft}}

== Cultural Properties ==
; Prefectural Cultural Properties (Nagano Prefecture Treasures)
* The main hall of Kumano Izuhaya Shrine (designated on August 15, 1994)

; Municipal Cultural Properties (Nagano City)
* Wooden seated statues of {{ill|Amida Nyorai|ja|阿弥陀如来|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Maitreya|ja|弥勒菩薩|12=draft|12=draft}} (designated on January 20, 1993)
* {{ill|Breeding site for Black Salamanders on Mount Minakami|ja|皆神山のクロサンショウウオの産卵地|12=draft|12=draft}} (designated on November 1, 1967)

== Access ==
* A11roximately 30 minutes by car from {{ill|Nagano Station|ja|長野駅|12=draft|12=draft}} (JR East)
* A11roximately 30 minutes by car from the {{ill|Nagano Interchange|ja|長野インターチェンジ|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Jōshin-etsu Expressway|ja|上信越自動車道|12=draft|12=draft}}

